This involves the use of artificial intelligence techniques such as decision graphs and interview-based assessments, making it a likely fit for the cs.AI category.
2. cs.LG - The development of the formal model of jurisprudence involves the use of machine learning techniques to identify relevant dimensions and decision points. This makes it a possible fit for the cs.LG category.
3. cs.CL - The interview-based assessment process involves the use of natural language processing techniques to understand user responses and guide them through the decision graph. This makes it a possible fit for the cs.CL category.
4. cs.CY - The development of an internet-based system for self-assessment of legal rights involves issues related to cybersecurity and privacy, making it a possible fit for the cs.CY category.
5. cs.CR - The development of an internet-based system for self-assessment of legal rights involves issues related to legal compliance and regulation, making it a possible fit for the cs.CR category.
